sf:StreamForge_Catalog_Assistant a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Agent,
        prov:Entity,
        dp:AI_Agent ;
    rdfs:label "StreamForge Catalog Assistant"@en ;
    dctm:description """The StreamForge Catalog Assistant is a synthetic AI agent included to support examples of RAG over the StreamForge data catalog. It is used to explain how text-heavy documentation chunks and graph-heavy lineage facts can be surfaced to a language model through embedding generation.

This individual is useful for demonstrations where the assistant must answer questions like who owns a data product, what upstream datasets a metric depends on, and where to find the authoritative documentation for an analytics definition."""@en ;
    skos:definition "An AI agent that answers questions about StreamForge data products, documentation, and lineage using embeddings and graph context."@en ;
    skos:editorialNote "Included to support narrative examples in the book about agentic interfaces to data catalogs."@en ;
    skos:note "An AI agent that answers questions about StreamForge data products, documentation, and lineage using embeddings and graph context."@en,
        "Included to support narrative examples in the book about agentic interfaces to data catalogs."@en,
        "Synthetic example AI agent for StreamForge."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note "StreamForge Catalog Assistant has definition An AI agent that answers questions about StreamForge data products, documentation, and lineage using embeddings and graph context."@en,
        """StreamForge Catalog Assistant has description The StreamForge Catalog Assistant is a synthetic AI agent included to support examples of RAG over the StreamForge data catalog. It is used to explain how text-heavy documentation chunks and graph-heavy lineage facts can be surfaced to a language model through embedding generation.

This individual is useful for demonstrations where the assistant must answer questions like who owns a data product, what upstream datasets a metric depends on, and where to find the authoritative documentation for an analytics definition."""@en .

