docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_01 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 01"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 1 ;
    docs:chunk_text "StreamForge creator engagement improved in Q3 2025, but gains were uneven across creator cohorts and upload frequencies. This report summarizes creator-side engagement metrics, highlights drivers of change, and proposes data product improvements for Q4."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Summary"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 01 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 01 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_02 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 02"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 2 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Reporting period: Q3 2025 (2025-07-01 to 2025-09-30). Population: active creators with at least one upload in the last 90 days. Exclusions: policy-removed channels and test accounts."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Scope and time window"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 02 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 02 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 03"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 3 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Monthly active creators (MAC): +6.2%. Uploads per active creator: +3.1%. Creator retention (90-day): +1.4 pp. Creator time-to-first-view median improved from 46 minutes to 39 minutes. Creator monetization enrollment: flat (+0.2%)."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Key metrics (Q3 vs Q2)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 03 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 03 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_04 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 04"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 4 ;
    docs:chunk_text "1) Faster time-to-first-view correlated strongly with higher creator retention, especially for small channels (<10k subscribers). 2) Improvements concentrated in long-form video; short-form creators did not see comparable lift."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Drivers and observations (1–2)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 04 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 04 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_05 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 05"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 5 ;
    docs:chunk_text "3) Metadata completeness (title, tags, category) was the strongest predictor of search impressions for new uploads. 4) The creator onboarding funnel had a measurable drop at connect payout account, but this is outside the primary scope of this report."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Drivers and observations (3–4)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 05 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 05 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_06 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 06"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 6 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Intermittent missing tag fields in the video metadata feed during August. A small fraction of creator profiles contained stale country codes after an upstream identity change. Issues did not materially change Q3 directional results, but reduce confidence in cohort segmentation."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Data quality notes"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 06 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 06 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_07 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 07"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 7 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Prioritize the Video Metadata data product to improve completeness and freshness of tags and categories. Add a creator-facing metadata quality indicator. Publish a weekly Creator Engagement Snapshot. Add SLAs for metadata freshness and completeness aligned with creator experience metrics (time-to-first-view and impressions)."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Recommendations for Q4"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 07 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 07 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025_Chunk_08 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 08"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 8 ;
    docs:chunk_text "How much of time-to-first-view improvement came from ranking changes vs metadata improvements? Can we isolate the short-form creator cohort and design targeted metadata guidance?"@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Open questions"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Engagement_Report_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 08 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Engagement Report Q3 2025 Chunk 08 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_01 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 01"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 1 ;
    docs:chunk_text """The Creator Growth metric is an executive KPI intended to summarize whether the StreamForge creator ecosystem is expanding in a sustainable way. It is designed for high-level dashboards and strategic reporting, not for diagnosing individual creator performance.

The metric is sensitive to both creator supply (how many creators are producing content and reaching engagement thresholds) and audience demand (whether viewers are engaging with creator content). It should be interpreted alongside supporting KPIs such as retention, new creator onboarding, and content category mix."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "What the metric is for"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 01 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 01 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_02 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 02"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 2 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Conceptually, Creator Growth increases when:
- more creators cross the 'active creator' threshold,
- existing creators increase their sustained engagement,
- and the distribution of engagement is not dominated by a tiny number of outliers.

A simple (illustrative) construction combines:
- count of active creators,
- median engagement per creator,
- and growth rate of creator cohorts over a reporting window.

Exact parameter values and thresholds are maintained as part of the metric specification and may evolve with governance review."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Definition (conceptual)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 02 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 02 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 03"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 3 ;
    docs:chunk_text """The computation is derived from the SF Creator Insights Dataset. Required inputs include creator-level KPIs such as:
- play counts
- unique viewers
- engagement rate
- retention proxies

Because the metric is computed from aggregated creator KPIs, upstream data quality issues (missing events, broken joins) typically manifest as sudden metric discontinuities. The computation run should therefore enforce strict validation on input freshness and completeness."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Computation inputs"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 03 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 03 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_04 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 04"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 4 ;
    docs:chunk_text """The executive dashboard uses a reporting window aligned to business cadence (e.g., trailing 28 days). The computation run applies this window to creator KPIs, aggregates to the metric level, and publishes a snapshot.

Snapshots are versioned by date and should be treated as immutable. If a recomputation is required (e.g., backfill corrections), publish a new snapshot with a new version identifier rather than overwriting historical values."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Windowing and snapshot logic"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 04 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 04 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_05 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 05"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 5 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Interpretation guidelines:
- Short-term volatility may occur due to product experiments, seasonal effects, or data pipeline incidents.
- A sustained increase over multiple windows is stronger evidence of ecosystem growth.
- Compare the metric against segment-level analyses (e.g., demographics and region) to understand *where* growth is happening.

Governance note: if metric definitions change, the change must be communicated to consumers and recorded in a data contract so that historical comparisons remain meaningful."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Interpretation guidance"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:Contract ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 05 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 05 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026_Chunk_06 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 06"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 6 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Related analyses include:
- Play video demographics summary (Q1–Q4 2025)
- Creator Insights aggregation runbook
- Regional acquisition and retention decomposition

These documents together support RAG-style question answering such as: 'How is Creator Growth computed?', 'What data feeds the metric?', and 'What demographic shifts occurred in 2025 that may affect creator growth?'"""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Link to related analyses"@en ;
    docs:has_topic docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026,
        docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Growth_Metric_Definition_Memo_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 06 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Growth Metric Definition Memo 2026 Chunk 06 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_01 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 01"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 1 ;
    docs:chunk_text """The Creator Insights Aggregation produces the SF Creator Insights Dataset, a curated table of creator KPIs used by dashboards, reporting, and downstream metric computations. It consolidates engagement events into creator-level aggregates and applies standard filters, normalization, and windowing.

Primary output: SF Creator Insights Dataset.
Secondary outputs: run metadata, validation summaries, and intermediate aggregates used for debugging."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Purpose and outputs"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 01 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 01 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_02 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 02"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 2 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Inputs:
- Engagement Events Dataset (event stream, normalized)
- Video Metadata Dataset (video → creator mapping and content attributes)
- Creator Profile Dataset (creator reference data and eligibility flags)

All three inputs are required. If any input fails freshness thresholds, the run is considered degraded and must not publish outputs to production dashboards."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Inputs"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 02 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 02 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 03"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 3 ;
    docs:chunk_text """High-level transformation steps:
1) Filter engagement events to eligible events and valid account/video ids.
2) Join events to video metadata to map events to creators.
3) Join to creator profile reference data (tier, region, account status).
4) Aggregate by creator and reporting window to compute KPIs (plays, unique viewers, engagement rate, etc.).
5) Normalize and apply standard definitions (e.g., deduping retry bursts).
6) Publish curated results to SF Creator Insights Dataset."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Transformations (high-level)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 03 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 03 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_04 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 04"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 4 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Quality checks include:
- Completeness of joins (event→video, video→creator)
- Distribution checks on key metrics (outliers, zeros, negative values)
- Volume regression checks (unexpected drops/spikes by region)
- Schema conformance validation

Failure handling:
- Hard failures stop the run.
- Soft failures publish output to a quarantine location and alert the Analytics Engineering Team."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Quality checks"@en ;
    docs:has_topic skos:ConceptScheme ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 04 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 04 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_05 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 05"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 5 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Provenance is recorded using PROV-O:
- The aggregation run is a prov:Activity (dp:Data_Analysis_Activity).
- Input datasets are prov:Entity assets.
- Output dataset is generated by the activity.
- The Analytics Engineering Team is associated with the activity.

This structure enables automated embedding-note generation and supports question answering such as: 'What datasets were used to produce SF Creator Insights?' and 'Which team ran the aggregation?'"""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Provenance and traceability"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 05 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 05 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_06 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 06"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 6 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Schedule: the aggregation is typically run daily, with additional ad-hoc runs during major product launches.

Operational constraints:
- Completion time target: under 30 minutes.
- Freshness requirements: engagement events must be available within a defined latency window.
- Publishing rules: do not overwrite prior snapshots without a version identifier.

If SLAs are missed, downstream metrics (e.g., Creator Growth) may be stale for dashboards."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Operational schedule and SLAs"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 06 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 06 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_07 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 07"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 7 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Common failure modes:
- Partial ingestion of engagement events causing artificial volume drops
- Missing video metadata due to upstream schema change
- Creator reference data drift (stale account status)
- Unexpected spikes from client retry storms

Mitigation:
- Validate input dataset freshness and schema before running aggregation.
- Use regression checks on event volumes and join completeness.
- Maintain a rollback plan for publishing outputs."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Common failure modes"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 07 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 07 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026_Chunk_08 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 08"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 8 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Downstream consumers include:
- Executive dashboards that display creator KPIs
- Metric computations such as Creator Growth
- Ad-hoc analyses (demographics, regional trends)

Because downstream systems assume stable KPI definitions, changes to the aggregation logic must be coordinated via a data contract and communicated to consumers before deployment."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Downstream dependencies"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:Contract ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Creator_Insights_Aggregation_Runbook_2026 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 08 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Creator Insights Aggregation Runbook 2026 Chunk 08 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_01 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 01"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 1 ;
    docs:chunk_text "On 2025-09-01 a regression in video metadata freshness caused the cataloged metadata dataset to lag real-time updates by several hours. The incident affected personalization cold-start behavior and search indexing for newly uploaded videos. This report documents impact, timeline, root cause, and corrective actions."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Summary"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 01 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 01 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_02 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 02"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 2 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Window of impact: 2025-09-01 08:20 UTC to 2025-09-01 16:05 UTC. Metadata lag: up to 6.4 hours at peak. User impact: reduced impressions and slower indexing for new uploads; elevated not relevant feedback in new-content cohorts. Internal impact: downstream jobs consumed stale timestamps, triggering feature drift alerts."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Impact"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 02 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 02 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 03"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 3 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Primary signal: freshness SLA monitor breached for the Video Metadata dataset. Secondary signal: downstream model feature drift alerts spiked for timestamp-derived features."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Detection"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 03 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 03 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_04 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 04"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 4 ;
    docs:chunk_text "08:20 freshness SLA breach detected. 08:35 incident declared; DRE engaged. 09:10 suspected backlog in ingestion pipeline. 11:40 identified retry storm in metadata enrichment. 13:15 mitigation applied by throttling retries and clearing stuck partitions. 16:05 freshness returned to normal; incident resolved."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Timeline (UTC)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 04 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 04 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_05 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 05"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 5 ;
    docs:chunk_text "A deployment changed retry behavior in the metadata enrichment job. Malformed payloads triggered repeated retries, saturating the queue and delaying partitions. The system lacked a circuit breaker for repeated failures on the same payload class."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Root cause"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 05 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 05 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_06 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 06"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 6 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Add circuit breaker and dead-letter routing for malformed payloads. Rate-limit retries and cap max retry time per partition. Introduce payload validation earlier in ingestion."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Corrective actions (engineering controls)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 06 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 06 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_07 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 07"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 7 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Extend catalog checks to include freshness monotonicity and timestamp plausibility rules."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Corrective actions (catalog checks)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 07 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 07 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression_Chunk_08 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 08"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 8 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Owner: Video Metadata data product team. Deadline: implement circuit breaker and catalog validation rules by 2025-09-20. Verification: replay incident window and confirm SLA compliance under fault injection."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Follow-up"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Incident_Report_Video_Metadata_Freshness_Regression ;
    dp:embedding_note "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 08 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Incident Report Video Metadata Freshness Regression Chunk 08 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_01 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 01"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 1 ;
    docs:chunk_text "This Q3 2025 review assesses StreamForge personalization performance across home feed ranking, Up Next, and notification targeting. It summarizes model metrics, user outcomes, and known risks to establish a stable baseline for Q4 experiments and to identify data product priorities affecting model quality."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Summary"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 01 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 01 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_02 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 02"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 2 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Reporting period: Q3 2025 (2025-07-01 to 2025-09-30). Surfaces: Home feed, Up Next, Notifications. Regions: global, with separate monitoring for India and Brazil."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Scope and time window"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 02 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 02 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 03"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 3 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Watch time per daily active user: +2.0%. Session starts per user: +1.1%. Not interested feedback rate: +0.4 pp (worse). Complaint rate (recommendation relevance): +0.2 pp (worse). Creator distribution: more concentrated in top 1% channels (+0.6 pp share)."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "User outcome summary (Q3 vs Q2)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 03 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 03 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_04 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 04"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 4 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Offline AUC improved modestly for home feed ranking (+0.3%), but calibration drift increased in August. User embeddings refreshed less frequently than expected for a subset of users due to a pipeline backlog."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Model and data signals (performance and drift)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 04 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 04 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_05 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 05"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 5 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Video metadata freshness had measurable impact on cold-start performance for new uploads and new creators. Category and tag coverage remains inconsistent across languages, affecting semantic retrieval features."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Model and data signals (metadata and language)"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 05 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 05 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_06 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 06"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 6 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Concentration risk: personalization reinforces already-large channels; mitigate with exploration controls and fairness-aware re-ranking. Drift risk: August calibration issues suggest instability in timestamp-derived features; mitigate with feature sanity checks and freshness SLAs. Trust risk: rising not interested feedback indicates relevance mismatch; mitigate with cohort-specific tuning and better negative-signal modeling."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Risks and mitigations"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 06 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 06 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_07 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 07"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 7 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Enforce a strict SLA for Video Metadata Freshness and validate timestamp monotonicity. Add monitoring for embedding refresh delays and backpressure in the feature pipeline. Run an experiment to reduce channel concentration without reducing watch time. Improve multilingual tag normalization as a data product enhancement rather than a model-side patch."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Recommendations for Q4"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 07 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 07 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025_Chunk_08 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 08"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 8 ;
    docs:chunk_text "Approve prioritization of metadata freshness work (pipeline plus catalog validation) over new model architecture changes for the first half of Q4."@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Decisions requested"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Personalization_Performance_Review_Q3_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 08 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Personalization Performance Review Q3 2025 Chunk 08 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_01 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 01"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 1 ;
    docs:chunk_text """This quarterly-style narrative summarizes demographic engagement patterns for StreamForge play_video events across Q1–Q4 2025. The goal is not only to report counts, but to explain the *drivers* of observed changes, note data quality caveats, and identify implications for product strategy and governance.

Across 2025, total play_video volume grew steadily, with the strongest seasonal acceleration in late Q3 and Q4. Growth was not uniform across demographic segments: younger cohorts drove most absolute volume, while several mid-life segments showed improving engagement depth (e.g., longer sessions per active user). Regional shifts partially explain quarter-to-quarter variation; policy changes around content recommendations also created measurable discontinuities.

This report is derived from the Engagement Events Dataset joined with Video Metadata (category, language, region, moderation flags) and Creator Profile reference data. It is intended for business readers; technical details (filters, joins, and data checks) are included in a later section."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Executive summary"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:SF_Engagement_Events_Dataset,
        sf:Video ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 01 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 01 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_02 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 02"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 2 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Event scope: play_video events represent user-initiated or autoplay-initiated video plays that exceed the minimum playback threshold (see pipeline configuration for threshold). We count plays, unique viewers, and repeat plays where relevant.

Demographic attributes: demographic segments are derived from account-level data (self-declared where available, otherwise inferred per internal policy). The report uses age bands and region groupings consistent with 2025 executive dashboards.

Time windows: Q1 (Jan–Mar), Q2 (Apr–Jun), Q3 (Jul–Sep), Q4 (Oct–Dec). Several platform experiments occurred mid-year; interpretations note when a trend is likely an artifact of product change rather than organic shift.

Exclusions: known bot traffic, internal test accounts, and videos removed for policy violations are excluded unless explicitly stated."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Definitions and scope"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:SF_Creator_Profile_Dataset ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 02 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 02 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_03 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 03"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 3 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Headline play_video metrics (illustrative):

| Quarter | Total Plays | Unique Viewers | Plays / Viewer |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| Q1 2025 | 1.10B | 120M | 9.2 |
| Q2 2025 | 1.18B | 123M | 9.6 |
| Q3 2025 | 1.31B | 128M | 10.2 |
| Q4 2025 | 1.49B | 135M | 11.0 |

Interpretation: Q3–Q4 acceleration is driven by (a) increased recommendation relevance for short-form content, (b) higher average session length, and (c) regional growth in new-user acquisition. The ratio plays/viewer increased more than unique viewers, indicating deeper engagement rather than just reach expansion."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Headline metrics by quarter"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 03 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 03 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_04 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 04"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 4 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Age segments remain the dominant driver of engagement volume. The youngest cohorts contribute most plays, but mid-life cohorts show a higher fraction of repeat viewing in several categories (education, news explainers, and long-form creators).

Illustrative share-of-plays by age band:

| Age Band | Share Q1 | Share Q2 | Share Q3 | Share Q4 |
|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|
| Under 18 | 14% | 13% | 12% | 12% |
| 18–34 | 46% | 45% | 44% | 43% |
| 35–54 | 30% | 31% | 32% | 33% |
| 55+ | 10% | 11% | 12% | 12% |

Takeaway: engagement share slowly shifted from 18–34 to 35–54 and 55+ over the year. This does not imply churn in younger cohorts; rather, growth rates were relatively higher in older cohorts."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Age segments overview (Q1–Q4 2025)"@en ;
    docs:has_topic skos:ConceptScheme ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 04 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 04 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_05 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 05"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 5 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Regional growth explains a substantial fraction of Q3–Q4 play increases. Several markets showed increased conversion from casual browsing to repeat viewing after localized recommendation tuning.

Language-level patterns: growth was concentrated in a small number of language communities with strong creator ecosystems. In regions where creator supply lagged demand, growth in unique viewers outpaced growth in plays/viewer; where creator supply was strong, plays/viewer increased.

Caveat: regional segmentation depends on account and device signals; privacy-preserving transformations can introduce mild lag in attribution. The report emphasizes directional trends over exact point estimates for small regions."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Regional effects and language"@en ;
    docs:has_topic sf:Video ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 05 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 05 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_06 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 06"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 6 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Changes in content category mix correlate with demographic shifts. For example, education and DIY categories grew disproportionately in 35–54 and 55+ cohorts. Short-form entertainment remained dominant for under-18 and 18–34.

Creator ecosystem effects: creator churn and onboarding in certain categories created supply-side changes that appear as demand-side shifts if not accounted for. When interpreting demographic changes, cross-check against the Creator Insights Dataset to ensure that a category’s play increase is not simply driven by an influx of high-performing creators."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Category mix and creator ecosystem"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:SF_Creator_Insights_Dataset ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 06 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 06 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_07 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 07"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 7 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Automated validation checks were applied before summarization:
- Schema conformance of key fields (event time, video id, account id)
- Duplicate detection for high-frequency client retries
- Bot and internal traffic exclusions
- Join completeness thresholds for video metadata and creator reference data

Limitations:
- Demographic attributes may be missing or stale for some accounts.
- Some regions have stronger privacy transformations, reducing granularity.
- Recommendation experiments can cause step-changes that mimic organic trends.

Recommendation: treat quarter-to-quarter comparisons as robust at aggregate levels, but avoid over-interpreting small segment movements without corroborating evidence."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Data quality checks and limitations"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 07 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 07 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_08 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 08"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 8 ;
    docs:chunk_text """The two most plausible drivers of 2025 demographic mix changes are:

1) Product experience improvements (recommendation relevance, session continuity) that disproportionately improved retention for mid-life cohorts.
2) Regional acquisition growth that introduced new audience segments with different viewing preferences.

A secondary driver is creator supply: categories with new creator onboarding tended to expand beyond their historical demographic base.

This report should be paired with the Creator Growth metric snapshot to evaluate whether increased plays in a segment translate into sustainable creator ecosystem growth (e.g., more creators reaching monetization thresholds)."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Interpretation: what changed and why"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:Creator_Growth_Metric_Snapshot_2026_02_08 ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 08 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 08 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_09 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 09"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 9 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Demographic insights inform governance decisions in three areas:

- Privacy: segments with sparse data require stricter aggregation thresholds.
- Content policy: higher exposure of certain cohorts to sensitive categories may require additional guardrails.
- IP and rights: as older cohorts grow, demand for legacy media content increases, raising the likelihood of copyrighted uploads and reuse.

Governance actions should be applied at the asset level (e.g., video and derived datasets), and enforced consistently across data products consuming engagement events."""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Implications for governance and policy"@en ;
    docs:has_topic dp:Permission,
        dp:Policy,
        dp:Prohibition ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 09 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 09 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025_Chunk_10 a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Entity,
        docs:Document_Chunk,
        dp:Catalog_Asset ;
    rdfs:label "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 10"@en ;
    docs:chunk_index 10 ;
    docs:chunk_text """Recommended follow-ups:

- Segment-level retention decomposition: identify which cohorts drive the plays/viewer increase.
- Category-by-demographic interaction analysis: determine whether category mix explains demographic shifts.
- Regional cohort analysis: separate acquisition-driven growth from engagement-driven growth.
- Audit of demographic attribute refresh cadence and missingness.

Deliverables:
- Updated quarterly summary (this document)
- Updated Creator Insights aggregation outputs
- Creator Growth metric snapshot for executive dashboards"""@en ;
    docs:chunk_title "Recommendations and next analyses"@en ;
    docs:is_chunk_of docs:Play_Video_Demographics_Quarterly_Report_2025 ;
    dp:embedding_note "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 10 is an instance of Catalog Asset."@en,
        "Play Video Demographics Quarterly Report 2025 Chunk 10 is an instance of Document Chunk."@en .

