dp:Sidecar a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Sidecar"@en ;
    rdfs:subClassOf _:nc0b2aa5d5f8947168b4edb4c3a148918b9,
        owl:Thing,
        dp:Sidecar ;
    owl:equivalentClass _:nc0b2aa5d5f8947168b4edb4c3a148918b9,
        dp:Sidecar ;
    skos:definition "A data product sidecar is a process that shares the execution context of a data product and is only responsible for domain-agnostic and cross-cutting concerns such as policy execution. In addition to policy execution, the sidecar process can be extended to implement other standardized features of a data product such as discovery. Dehghani, Zhamak. Data Mesh: Delivering Data-Driven Value at Scale (p. 4). O'Reilly Media. Kindle Edition."@en,
        "Sidecars provide a convenient architectural location for enforcing semantic constraints, turning models and validation rules into executable components attached to data products."@en ;
    skos:note "A data product sidecar is a process that shares the execution context of a data product and is only responsible for domain-agnostic and cross-cutting concerns such as policy execution. In addition to policy execution, the sidecar process can be extended to implement other standardized features of a data product such as discovery. Dehghani, Zhamak. Data Mesh: Delivering Data-Driven Value at Scale (p. 4). O'Reilly Media. Kindle Edition."@en,
        "Sidecars provide a convenient architectural location for enforcing semantic constraints, turning models and validation rules into executable components attached to data products."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note "Sidecar has definition A data product sidecar is a process that shares the execution context of a data product and is only responsible for domain-agnostic and cross-cutting concerns such as policy execution. In addition to policy execution, the sidecar process can be extended to implement other standardized features of a data product such as discovery. Dehghani, Zhamak. Data Mesh: Delivering Data-Driven Value at Scale (p. 4). O'Reilly Media. Kindle Edition."@en,
        "Sidecar has definition Sidecars provide a convenient architectural location for enforcing semantic constraints, turning models and validation rules into executable components attached to data products."@en .

